The MPC will decide whether it is going to cut interest rates for the first time since March 2018. Some economists are predicting a 25 per cent cut to bring the repo rate down to 6.5 per cent. What are the chances for a bit of relief for the indebted? Transaction Capital CEO, David Hurwitz and Tumisho Grater, Economic Strategist at Novare join CNBC Africa for more....